MODULE: src/utils/output-segmenter
FILES: output-segmenter.js
RESPONSIBILITY: Smart text segmentation at logical boundaries (code blocks, paragraphs) for Telegram messages
KEY_FILES:
- output-segmenter.js: 1 exported function + 4 private helpers, ~130 lines. Pure string transformation.
DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: none (no external dependencies)
- imported-by: src/bot/telegram.js (createEditableStreamPublisher render() function)
TRAPS:
- Code block detection counts ``` occurrences — odd count means inside a block. This counts inline triple-backticks too; strings with malformed fences will misdetect.
- Splits at paragraph (\n\n) first, then newline (\n), then space — never hard-cuts at arbitrary byte boundary unless forced (no logical boundary found).
- Default maxChunkSize is 3800, NOT 4096 — Telegram limit is 4096 but 3800 gives safety margin for metadata overhead.
- findCodeBlockEnd searches for closing ``` AFTER the opening fence — if closing fence is missing (incomplete stream), it returns maxChunkSize as fallback (hard cut).
- Replaces splitMessage() in the render() function inside createEditableStreamPublisher — NOT in the cross-channel push path (subscribeCrossChannel still uses splitMessage).
CHANGELOG:
- 2026-03-22 | add: initial module for F-020 smart output segmentation
UPDATED: 2026-03-22
